properties.headline: Lakeshore Flood Watch issued January 9 at 3:20AM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Milwaukee/Sullivan has issued a
Lakeshore Flood Watch...Which is in effect from late Friday night
through late Saturday night.

* Winds...Northeast at 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph
possible.

* Waves...10 to 12 feet.

* Impacts...Due to the high Lake Michigan water levels, flooding
of beaches and roads is possible near the lakeshore. The high
waves may cause erosion along Lake Michigan.
properties.instruction:
A Lakeshore Flood Watch means that conditions favorable for
lakeshore flooding are expected to develop. Residents on or near
the shore should take action to protect property...and listen for
later statements or warnings.

NWSheadline: LAKESHORE FLOOD WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE FRIDAY NIGHT THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
